Poor digital communication can lead to serious misunderstandings and negative consequences. For example, if a student sends an email to a professor without a proper subject line, greeting, or respectful tone, it may be considered unprofessional and ignored. This can result in missed opportunities or lack of response.

Such situations can be avoided by following proper email etiquette, including using a clear subject line, polite language, and a structured format. It is important to communicate respectfully and professionally in academic and professional environments to create a positive impression.
